> >>>see for example:
> >>>
> >>>https://stats.stackexchange.com/q/69882/1934
> >>>
> >>>Or let me give a more technical explanation based on the standard RE
> model:
> >>>
> >>>dat <- escalc(measure="RR", ai=tpos, bi=tneg, ci=cpos, di=cneg,
> data=dat.bcg)
> >>>res <- rma(yi, vi, data=dat)
